    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-10T17:22:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-10T17:22:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895B.10/10–1051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-10T17:22:00-05:00"
                            >October 10, 1951—5:22 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. Dept today presented Yang with check for $12,155,714 who accepted the terms
                    of payment as contained in <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> by signing <pb
                        facs="1027" n="1011" xml:id="pg_1011"/> receipt set forth in <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 238.<note n="1" xml:id="d625fn1">Dated
                        September 26, <ref target="#pg_964">p. 964</ref>.</note> Dept issued fol
                    press release which was agreed with Amb Yang:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The United States has paid to the Government of the <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                            >ROK</gloss> $12,155,714 in settlement for 63,051,922,270 <hi
                            rend="italic">won</hi>, Korean currency which has been made available by
                        the <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> through Jul 31, 1951 for direct sale
                        to US personnel, for their personal expenditures, it was announced today by
                        the Depts of State, Defense and Treas.</p>
                    <p>“The payment is without prejudice to settlement for other amounts of currency
                        made available by the <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> under terms of the
                        Financial Agreement of Jul 28, 1950.</p>
                    <p>“The Financial Agreement provides that negots for settlement of any claims
                        shall be deferred to a time or times mutually satis to the US and to the
                            <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>. The payment to the Govt of the
                            <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> at this time is intended to assist
                        the Korean Govt in supplying essential commodities for the war-torn Korean
                        economy, over and above the types of relief supplies being brought in by the
                        UN Command.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
